# CivicPulse — Comprehensive System Documentation
## Part 3 of 3: Frontend, Design System, Deployment & Operations

---

## Chapter 14: Frontend Components

### 14.1 Global Layout & State

#### [app/layout.js](file:///d:/Projects/app/layout.js) — Root Layout
The root layout wraps every page. It:
- Imports global CSS ([app/globals.css](file:///d:/Projects/app/globals.css))
- Wraps children in `<UserProvider>` (React Context for authentication state)
- Wraps in `<I18nProvider>` (internationalization)
- Sets default metadata (title, description)

#### [lib/contexts/UserContext.js](file:///d:/Projects/lib/contexts/UserContext.js) — Authentication State
The most critical piece of client-side state. [UserProvider](file:///d:/Projects/lib/contexts/UserContext.js#6-33) wraps the app and exposes `{ user, setUser, loading, logout }`.

**Initialization:** On mount, it calls `GET /api/auth/me`. If the JWT cookie is valid, `user` is populated. If not, `user` is `null`. During this check, `loading` is `true` — all pages show a spinner while the check happens.

**Usage in any component:**
```javascript
const { user, loading, logout } = useUser();
// user.role, user.name, user.email, user.wardId, user.departmentId
```

**Logout:** Calls `POST /api/auth/logout` (clears cookie) then redirects to `/login`.

---

### 14.2 DashboardLayout ([components/DashboardLayout.js](file:///d:/Projects/components/DashboardLayout.js))

The shared sidebar + header wrapper used by all authenticated dashboards. Not a server component — it's a Client Component (`'use client'`).

**Structure:**
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              HEADER (sticky)            │
│  [hamburger]  [spacer]  [lang] [bell]  │
├──────────┬──────────────────────────────┤
│          │                              │
│ SIDEBAR  │       PAGE CONTENT           │
│  (fixed) │       (scrollable)           │
│          │                              │
│ [ Logo ] │                              │
│ [ Nav  ] │                              │
│ [ User ] │                              │
│ [Logout] │                              │
└──────────┴──────────────────────────────┘
```

**Navigation is role-specific.** The [getNavKey(role, pathname)](file:///d:/Projects/components/DashboardLayout.js#110-134) function maps the user's role to the correct navigation set:

| Role | Nav Set | Items |
|------|---------|-------|
| CITIZEN | `citizen` | Dashboard, Report Issue, My Issues, Map, Public |
| FIELD_OFFICER | `department` | Dashboard, My Issues, Resolved, Performance, Profile |
| DEPARTMENT_MANAGER | `municipal` | Dashboard, My Officers, SLA Monitoring |
| MUNICIPAL_COMMISSIONER | `commissioner` | Dashboard, City Map, All Issues, Departments, Issues Master, Create Staff |
| SYSTEM_ADMIN | `admin` | Dashboard, Users, Create User, Departments, All Issues, Analytics |

**Responsive behavior:**
- On mobile (`< lg breakpoint`): Sidebar is hidden. Hamburger button toggles it with a slide-in animation. Black overlay (`bg-black/60`) covers the content behind the open sidebar.
- On desktop (`>= lg`): Sidebar is always visible as a fixed column.

**Active state:** A nav item is "active" if `pathname === item.href` or `pathname.startsWith(item.href + '/')`. Active items have a gold left border indicator (`bg-gold/10 text-gold border border-gold/20`).

---

### 14.3 DashboardProtection ([components/DashboardProtection.js](file:///d:/Projects/components/DashboardProtection.js))

A client component that wraps dashboard pages with an additional client-side role check. Even though the Edge Middleware handles routing, this provides a UI-level safety net:

```javascript
// Usage:
<DashboardProtection allowedRoles={['CITIZEN', 'citizen']}>
  <CitizenDashboard />
</DashboardProtection>
```

If the user's role is not in `allowedRoles`, they see an "Access Denied" message instead of the page content.

---

### 14.4 ImageUploader ([components/ImageUploader.jsx](file:///d:/Projects/components/ImageUploader.jsx))

Handles the image upload flow for the report form.

**Features:**
- Drag-and-drop or click to select files
- Accepts up to 3 images
- Shows a preview grid
- Each image can be removed individually
- **Client-side compression** before upload using `browser-image-compression`
- Upload progress indicator during Cloudinary upload
- On upload, calls `POST /api/upload` and stores `{ url, publicId }`

**Compression settings:**
```javascript
{
  maxSizeMB: 1,          // Max 1MB per image
  maxWidthOrHeight: 1920, // Max dimension 1920px
  useWebWorker: true     // Non-blocking compression
}
```

---

### 14.5 LocationPicker ([components/LocationPicker.jsx](file:///d:/Projects/components/LocationPicker.jsx))

Interactive Leaflet map for selecting the issue location.

**Features:**
- Click anywhere on the map to drop a pin
- Pin is draggable for fine-tuning
- Shows the resulting coordinates and address
- Reverse geocoding: converts clicked coordinates to a human-readable address
- Ward selector dropdown — citizen picks which ward the issue is in
- Coordinates are stored as `[lng, lat]` for MongoDB GeoJSON compatibility

**Libraries:** `react-leaflet`, `leaflet`

---

### 14.6 IssueMap ([components/IssueMap.jsx](file:///d:/Projects/components/IssueMap.jsx))

A read-only map showing all issues as markers. Used on the public map page and in dashboards.

**Features:**
- Loads issues from `GET /api/issues/public`
- Color-coded markers by status (green=resolved, yellow=in-progress, blue=assigned, gray=pending)
- Cluster nearby markers using `react-leaflet-cluster` to prevent UI overload
- Clicking a marker opens a popup via `<IssuePopup />`

---

