## Chapter 21: Developer Quick-Start Guide

### 21.1 Prerequisites

- Node.js ≥18.17.0
- MongoDB running locally (or MongoDB Atlas connection string)
- Git

### 21.2 First-Time Setup

```bash
# 1. Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/yourorg/civic-issue-system.git
cd civic-issue-system

# 2. Install dependencies
npm install

# 3. Create local environment file
cp .env.local.example .env.local
# Edit .env.local with your values

# 4. Seed the database
npm run db:seed              # Creates departments
npm run db:seed-users        # Creates test users

# 5. Start development server
npm run dev
```

### 21.3 Test Credentials (After Seeding)

| Role | Email | Password |
|------|-------|---------|
| System Admin | admin@civicpulse.in | admin123 |
| Commissioner | commissioner@civicpulse.in | comm123 |
| Dept Manager (Roads) | roads.manager@civicpulse.in | dept123 |
| Field Officer (Ward 1) | officer.ward1@civicpulse.in | officer123 |
| Citizen | citizen@example.com | citizen123 |

### 21.4 Available Scripts

```bash
npm run dev         # Start development server (localhost:3000)
npm run build       # Production build
npm run start       # Start production server
npm run lint        # Run ESLint
npm run check       # Run startup configuration check
npm run test        # Run Jest test suite
npm run test:watch  # Jest in watch mode
npm run db:seed     # Seed departments
npm run db:seed-users # Seed users
npm run db:admin    # Create admin user only
npm run clean       # Remove .next and node_modules
npm run reset       # Clean + reinstall
```

### 21.5 Development Tips

1. **Hot reload:** Next.js dev server hot-reloads on file changes. API routes reload automatically.

2. **MongoDB connection:** The connection is cached in `global.mongoose` to prevent opening multiple connections in development (Next.js hot-reloads can re-run module code). If MongoDB is down, you get a descriptive error rather than a crash.

3. **JWT in dev:** Sessions persist for 7 days. To force a fresh login, call `POST /api/auth/logout` or delete the `token` cookie in DevTools.

4. **i18n hot-reload:** Translation changes require a page refresh (not just hot-reload) because i18next initializes once.

5. **AI features without API keys:** If Gemini/OpenAI keys are missing, the system falls back to keyword detection. The report form will still work but without AI auto-fill.

6. **Image uploads without Cloudinary:** If Cloudinary keys are missing, `POST /api/upload` will fail. Issues can still be submitted with empty `images: []`.

7. **Email without Resend:** All email functions check for `RESEND_API_KEY` at runtime and return `{ success: false }` gracefully. The application never crashes because of missing email config.

### 21.6 Testing

Jest is configured with:
- [jest.config.mjs](file:///d:/Projects/jest.config.mjs) — Test environment: `jsdom` (for React component tests)
- [jest.setup.js](file:///d:/Projects/jest.setup.js) — Sets up `@testing-library/jest-dom` matchers
- [babel.config.cjs.bak](file:///d:/Projects/babel.config.cjs.bak) — Babel preset for transpiling JSX/ESM in tests

Test files are in `__tests__/` directory. Run individual test files:
```bash
npm test -- --testPathPattern="auth"
```

