## Appendix A: Glossary

| Term | Definition |
|------|-----------|
| **SLA** | Service Level Agreement — the deadline by which an issue must be resolved |
| **Ward** | A geographic subdivision of the municipality. 16 wards, grouped into 2 zones |
| **Zone** | North or South — each contains 8 wards |
| **Report ID** | Human-readable issue identifier (R00001, R00002, ...) |
| **Upvote** | Citizen endorsement of an existing issue, increases community priority |
| **Escalation** | Automatic promotion of an overdue issue to higher authority |
| **Penalty Points** | Points accumulated on a department for SLA breaches |
| **Detection Source** | How the issue category was determined (AI/manual) |
| **JWT** | JSON Web Token — encodes user identity for authentication |
| **ODM** | Object Document Mapper (Mongoose maps JavaScript objects to MongoDB documents) |
| **Edge Middleware** | Code that runs at CDN edge nodes, before the main server |
| **HTTP-only Cookie** | A cookie that JavaScript cannot read — protects against XSS attacks |
| **bcrypt** | Password hashing algorithm with configurable cost factor |

---

## Appendix B: Architecture Decision Records

### ADR 1: Custom JWT over NextAuth
We replaced NextAuth with custom JWT to: (1) have full control over token payload (wardId, departmentId), (2) simplify the role normalization logic, (3) avoid NextAuth's complex configuration for custom role-based routing.

### ADR 2: MongoDB over SQL
MongoDB was chosen for: (1) flexible schema for issues with variable fields (varying image counts, escalation history depth), (2) built-in geospatial query support (`2dsphere`), (3) natural JSON alignment with Next.js API routes.

### ADR 3: Gemini as Primary AI, OpenAI as Fallback
Gemini Flash provides: (1) image authenticity verification (unique feature), (2) faster response times, (3) lower cost per token. OpenAI gpt-4o-mini is the fallback since it's a proven, stable alternative.

### ADR 4: Ward System as Source of Truth
The [lib/wards.js](file:///d:/Projects/lib/wards.js) module is the single source of truth. All ward → zone → department mappings live here. This prevents data inconsistencies and makes the geography system maintainable from one place.

### ADR 5: Standalone Output for Deployment
`output: 'standalone'` creates a self-contained deployment artifact that works on any Node.js server, Docker container, or serverless platform without needing the entire `node_modules` directory.

